{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784788606758", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "我已经掌握了足够的研究背景。主要发现如下：\n1. **AnalyticKWS** (ACL Findings 2025, arXiv 2505.11817) —— 针对 KWS 的无样本类增量学习，是直接相关的竞争性工作，但该论文未被引用。\n2. **Kim et al., Interspeech 2024** —— “Few-Shot Keyword-Incremental Learning with Total Calibration” —— 又一篇直接相关的 KWS 增量学习论文，未被引用。\n3. **PNNs (Rusu et al., 2016)** —— 已被引用，并明确将其定位为不同方向（任务增量 vs 类增量）。\n\n我再针对 AnalyticKWS 进行一次检查，看看它是否解决了相同的问题。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "661d7789-02a0-4faf-820e-46fe5b9e77f1", "uuid": "7e834fff-391c-4cb4-9bbb-f741caf9b911"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784788606758", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-a116992f40ee62a5", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.11817\" | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, re, html\ntext = sys.stdin.read()\n# Extract abstract\nm = re.search(r'<blockquote class=\\\"abstract mathjax\\\">(.*?)</blockquote>', text, re.DOTALL)\nif m:\n    abstract = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '', m.group(1))\n    abstract = html.unescape(abstract)\n    print(abstract.strip()[:1500])\nelse:\n    print('Abstract not found')\n\"", "description": "Fetch AnalyticKWS abstract"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "661d7789-02a0-4faf-820e-46fe5b9e77f1", "uuid": "fb6f4378-ef9e-468c-8f30-3f607cec4218"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a116992f40ee62a5", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Abstract:Keyword spotting (KWS) offers a vital mechanism to identify spoken commands in voice-enabled systems, where user demands often shift, requiring models to learn new keywords continually over time. However, a major problem is catastrophic forgetting, where models lose their ability to recognize earlier keywords. Although several continual learning methods have proven their usefulness for reducing forgetting, most existing approaches depend on storing and revisiting old data to combat catastrophic forgetting. Though effective, these methods face two practical challenges: 1) privacy risks from keeping user data and 2) large memory and time consumption that limit deployment on small devices. To address these issues, we propose an exemplar-free Analytic Continual Learning (AnalyticKWS) method that updates model parameters without revisiting earlier data. Inspired by efficient learning principles, AnalyticKWS computes a closed-form analytical solution for model updates and requires only a single epoch of adaptation for incoming keywords. AnalyticKWS demands fewer computational resources by avoiding gradient-based updates and does not store old data. By eliminating the need for back-propagation during incremental learning, the model remains lightweight and efficient. As a result, AnalyticKWS meets the challenges mentioned earlier and suits resource-limited settings well. Extensive experiments on various datasets and settings show that AnalyticKWS consistently outperforms exi", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "661d7789-02a0-4faf-820e-46fe5b9e77f1", "uuid": "f8f3abb6-2048-4a40-b1cc-5f81b8b9f0dd", "timestamp": "2026-07-23T06:36:55.437Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "Abstract:Keyword spotting (KWS) offers a vital mechanism to identify spoken commands in voice-enabled systems, where user demands often shift, requiring models to learn new keywords continually over time. However, a major problem is catastrophic forgetting, where models lose their ability to recognize earlier keywords. Although several continual learning methods have proven their usefulness for reducing forgetting, most existing approaches depend on storing and revisiting old data to combat catastrophic forgetting. Though effective, these methods face two practical challenges: 1) privacy risks from keeping user data and 2) large memory and time consumption that limit deployment on small devices. To address these issues, we propose an exemplar-free Analytic Continual Learning (AnalyticKWS) method that updates model parameters without revisiting earlier data. Inspired by efficient learning principles, AnalyticKWS computes a closed-form analytical solution for model updates and requires only a single epoch of adaptation for incoming keywords. AnalyticKWS demands fewer computational resources by avoiding gradient-based updates and does not store old data. By eliminating the need for back-propagation during incremental learning, the model remains lightweight and efficient. As a result, AnalyticKWS meets the challenges mentioned earlier and suits resource-limited settings well. Extensive experiments on various datasets and settings show that AnalyticKWS consistently outperforms exi", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784788630966", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "重要发现。AnalyticKWS 解决了非常相似的问题（无样本、KWS 中的类增量学习），但采用了根本不同的方法（闭式解析解，而非模块化扩展）。它是 2025 年 5 月发表的，比这篇论文早了约 2 个月——属于同期/近期工作，但对于新颖性比较仍然值得注意。Kim 等人发表在 Interspeech 2024 上的论文也直接相关。\n\n我再简要检查一下 Kim 等人的论文。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "661d7789-02a0-4faf-820e-46fe5b9e77f1", "uuid": "f1298f0f-b1ec-4866-9896-32c8e99d0e5e"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784788630966", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-89010241d90261ba", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://www.isca-archive.org/interspeech_2024/kim24r_interspeech.html\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, re, html\ntext = sys.stdin.read()\n# Extract text\ntext = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)\ntext = html.unescape(text)\ntext = re.sub(r' +', ' ', text)\n# Find abstract section\nfor part in text.split('Abstract'):\n    if 'keyword' in part.lower():\n        print(part[:1000])\n        break\n\" 2>&1 | head -20", "description": "Fetch Kim et al. Interspeech 2024 abstract"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "661d7789-02a0-4faf-820e-46fe5b9e77f1", "uuid": "73c50b05-3c90-40c9-b0ea-e8416f071b88"}
